# INTEX2 — Laya Foundation Project Context

## Project Overview
This is a full-stack nonprofit case management and 
donor management platform for Laya Foundation, 
an anti-trafficking nonprofit serving girls in 
the Philippines. Modeled after Lighthouse Sanctuary.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React + TypeScript (Vite) in /frontend
- Backend: .NET 10 / C# in /backend/Intext2/Intext2
- Database: Azure SQL Database
- Deployment: Azure Static Web Apps (frontend) + 
  Azure App Service (backend)
- Auth: ASP.NET Identity with cookie-based auth
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions

## Key URLs
- Frontend: https://jolly-moss-00018721e.5.azurestaticapps.net
- Backend: https://intex-backend-maddie-ashaarbue3gkcagu.westus2-01.azurewebsites.net

## Database
- Server: intex-server-maddie.database.windows.net
- Database: intex-db
- Credentials stored in .NET User Secrets (never in code)

## Authentication
- Cookie-based auth (NOT JWT)
- Password policy: 14 chars minimum only
- Roles: Admin, Donor, Public
- Admin email: admin@intex.local
- Donor email: donor@lighthousesanctuary.org

## Security Already Implemented
- HTTPS/TLS via Azure
- HTTP → HTTPS redirect
- Cookie hardening (HttpOnly, SecurePolicy, SameSite)
- CSP header via Infrastructure/SecurityHeaders.cs
- HSTS in production
- RBAC on all CUD endpoints
- .NET User Secrets for credentials
- CORS configured for frontend domains

## File Structure
frontend/src/
  pages/
    public/ — Home, Login, ImpactDashboard, PrivacyPolicy
    admin/ — AdminDashboard, CaseloadInventory, Donors, 
              ProcessRecording, HomeVisitation, Reports,
              StaffManagement
  components/
    layout/ — Navbar, Footer, AdminSidebar
    ui/ — CookieConsent, ProtectedRoute
  context/ — AuthContext.tsx
  services/ — authApi.ts, mockData.ts
  types/ — AuthSession.ts

backend/Intext2/Intext2/
  Controllers/ — Auth, Residents, Supporters, Donations,
                 ProcessRecordings, HomeVisitations,
                 InterventionPlans, IncidentReports, Reports
  Models/ — 18 model files matching Azure SQL schema
  Data/ — ApplicationDbContext.cs
  Auth/ — AuthRoles.cs, AuthPolicies.cs
  Infrastructure/ — SecurityHeaders.cs
  Dtos/ — LoginDto, RegisterDto, AuthResponseDto, 
          DeleteConfirmDto
  Migrations/ — InitialCreate (Identity tables only)

## Domain Tables (already exist in Azure, populated with CSV data)
safehouses, partners, partner_assignments, supporters,
donations, in_kind_donation_items, donation_allocations,
residents, process_recordings, home_visitations,
education_records, health_wellbeing_records,
intervention_plans, incident_reports, social_media_posts,
safehouse_monthly_metrics, public_impact_snapshots

